node.text:
Life is so different right now, but in a way, I’m really grateful for the change. It has taught me a lot and shown me that nothing in life is permanent. You can rise up from anything. You can think new thoughts. You can learn something new. You can create new habits. You just have to decide - how are you going to show up? Sure, it may seem like there’s no point in doing that right now because of all of life’s uncertainties, but do you want to know one thing that needs you? YOU. The moments when you show up for yourself are when the magic happens. 
Its okay to feel anxious, unmotivated, and sad but also take a moment and appreciate that you are alive right now. You have the opportunity to open your eyes everyday. You are breathing. Your heart is beating. And if all you’re working on is yourself right now, YOU’RE DOING GREAT!!!! Its taken me all this time feel a spark of creativity and a little like me again and I’m so thankful that. Just keep making those baby steps everyday.
Your set back got nothing on your come back. ✨🤍
Thankful for this guy that’s sparked my love for boxing a few months back. We’re just getting started 😉 @robmorseiv !

node.title: Your set back got nothin on your comeback✨

node.text:
And that’s a wrap!!!  Season Bachelorette 17, it’s been real!  
•
It’s important to me that I acknowledge the gratitude I have for ABC and The Bachelor franchise.  Thank you for believing in me and giving me an opportunity to support our lead Katie, represent the BIPOC community, and most importantly, emphasize the power of women supporting other women!! I’ve loved every second of it, and I thank you Bachelor Nation for the love and support. Kaitlyn, it’s hard to find a co-host you can click so well with. I wouldn’t want to be a mentor with anyone else! Cannot wait for another season to be on your television screens! See you in the fall. Xoxo tayshia

node.text:
At approximately this time 365 days ago, I met you! It’s been a wild ride so far with our lives going a million miles an hour but how lucky are we to have had an amazing week together at the place where it all started AND we were to able to renew our wishes a year later?! WILD✨
Happy to have you by my side, Clarky. 143♥️ #happydaythatimetyou
